{"about_the_game":"<h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>What is Calendula?</strong></h2><i>Calendula is an experience. Calendula is a mystery. Calendula is a glass full of blood. Calendula is an experiment. Calendula is an atmospheric game. Calendula is a flower. Calendula is your deepest secret... </i><h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>About Calendula</strong></h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Calendula begins as a usual game... until it is not anymore.<br></li><li>The player's goal will be to <strong>unveil the mystery</strong> behind an apparently broken game, but it won't be easy. <br></li><li>Calendula's mechanics are entirely focused on the struggle of trying to start a game, <strong>exploring the limits of the 4th wall</strong> and breaking with conventions. <br></li><li>Calendula's aesthetics follows an increasing <strong>obscure atmosphere</strong>, plunging the player into a disturbing, thrilling experience.<br></li><li>The narrative is built within <strong>a labyrinth of metaphors and abstractions</strong>, ready to be unraveled. <br></li><li>Unlike other games, the player will feel as <strong>if things didn't work the way they should</strong>, similar to Twin Peaks' Red Room (David Lynch). <br></li><li>The player's journey goes from simple to complex, from bright to somber, <strong>from real to dreamlike</strong>. <br></li><li>To follow Calendula's path, the player will have to use his wit and think outside the box. In this case, a tiny oppressive box.<br><br>Please, remember this: <span class=\"bb_spoiler\">It is not your fault.</span></li></ul>","achievements":{"highlighted":[{"name":"Do you understand now?","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/427810/545a86e432171bce5f6cf28053d275bd8b93a55e.jpg"},{"name":"You need to rest","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/427810/d83831c127ebfdb949c358007b2a82b93e3e45c2.jpg"},{"name":"It's over","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/pub